The Ribeyrolles 1918 was an attempt to manufacture an automatic rifle for French forces during the First World War. Its official name was 'Carabine Mitrailleuse 1918' (Machine Carbine 1918 in English).

The Ribeyrolles featured a direct blow-back action, and was chambered for experimental 8×35mm rounds fed from a 25 round magazine. The gun itself had a stated effective range of 400 meters. The cartridge, arguably the first purpose-built intermediate cartridge ever produced, was created by necking down .351 Winchester. The gun was fitted with a lightweight bipod for shooting while prone or at the edge of a trench, and could mount a rifle bayonet identical to that of a Berthier Model 1907/15.

Due to numerous mechanical issues plaguing the design, the Carabine Mitrailleuse 1918 was ultimately rejected by the French military and never saw service during the war.

The Sith and loyal companion Lana Beniko from Star Wars the Old Republic (Swtor) by Bioware. Works best on 0.7-1.0. Training done on NAI.

V2 is a Locon which can be placed in LoRA folder on Automatic1111 1.5 so make sure to update otherwise place in Lyco folder.

Suggestions:

Note: I made a typo for the name of the expansion in training so you need to use it as "kofte" rather than the actual name kotfe. You can rename the file if you want but the trigger needs to be like below.

V2:

  • Main outfit: "LanaBenikoKofte" is enough to trigger as it is more consistent.

  • Little style bake and works well on many models I tested.

V2 was an experiment in learning how to use a better optimizer and to reduce style bake which worked very well. I hope you all enjoy.

V1:

  • Main outfit: "LanaBenikoKofte, scarf" add "turtleneck" if you want more focus on having it.

  • Her outfit works quite well from various angles but can bleed into certain other clothes so beware.

  • Adding more descriptors or putting things into Negative prompt can help get other clothes working better than they already do.

My favorite from Swtor and best Sith Waifu. I spent a good bit of time trying to get her consistent and can safely say it turned out pretty nice. I hope you all enjoy.

Feedback and reviews are always appreciated.

LoRA's good at generating the adult version of Groot in different styles and is pretty versatile, however, it's not as good at hyperrealism/photorealism as it is with digital art (paintings/comic book...). For more realistic images, I recommend to lower the strength. In general, 0.8-1 works fine, but if you feel the LoRA isn't getting your prompt as you'd like, you can try to experiment with lower values, and add in your prompt "adult" so the model doesn't mix traits of baby Groot in your generation.

Up until now, I've trained with a ratio of 9 white backgrounds and 1 gray background, but for better or worse the background image was monotonous.

Bruce Lorne Campbell (born June 22, 1958) is an American actor and filmmaker. He is best known for his role as Ash Williams in Sam Raimi's Evil Dead horror franchise, beginning with the short film Within the Woods (1978). He has also starred in many low-budget cult films such as Crimewave (1985), Maniac Cop (1988), Sundown: The Vampire in Retreat (1989), and Bubba Ho-Tep (2002).

On television, Campbell had leading roles in The Adventures of Brisco County, Jr. (1993–1994) and Jack of All Trades (2000), and a recurring role as Autolycus, King of Thieves in Hercules: The Legendary Journeys (1995–1999) and Xena: Warrior Princess (1995–1999). He played Sam Axe on the USA Network series Burn Notice (2007–2013) and reprised his role as Ash on the Starz series Ash vs. Evil Dead (2015–2018). He also appeared in The Escort (2015).

Campbell directed, produced, and starred in the documentaries Fanalysis (2002) and A Community Speaks (2004); co-wrote, directed, produced, and starred in the film Man with the Screaming Brain (2005); and directed, produced, and starred in a parody of his career My Name Is Bruce (2007).

Campbell is known for frequent collaborations with the aforementioned Raimi, his brother Ted, Josh Becker, and Scott Spiegel.

items.name: Grit
items.description:
Grit (SDXL 1.0) textures with irregularities (rust, grit, stains), useful for game assets or a vintage look. Created from an in-house photo dataset of textures, collected on a field trip. The Lora is intended as a texture creation helper, for tileable textures, but it also works in scenes to texture objects. It adds randomness and structure to various photos. (SDXL 1024x1024). Try to use weights around 1.5 for best textures, although even 0 will change the image a little (for the better).

Rate, like, and review to help people find the model on the site.

For tutorials and guides on generative AI applications in art, graphic design, 3D and AR/VR, check my website sandner.art in the section https://sandner.art/articles/ai/

Support my adventures by buying me a coffee: https://ko-fi.com/airesearch

Have fun rendering!
